Hey guys, that girl in the picture up there, that's me. Maybe it’s time for a little intro since it’s been a while? 

Adair Currie - wife, mom, a Bravo TV addict, a need for black iced coffee morning, noon, and night, and a passion to discover the love between two people and weave that story through the details of their wedding day. 

Adair is a family name. I was named after my father and he was named after his uncle. It has become such an important part of me, my name, my brand, that we wanted our daughter to also share the same legacy. Her name is Adair Lucille. Lucille is from my favorite actress of all time, Lucille Ball. 

I wear my heart of my sleeve.

I would rather ask for forgiveness than ask for permission. 

My hair is in a messy top knot 85% of the time, barely there makeup, and there's a good chance I'm also rocking denim. Denim is my security blanket.

Even though Weddings are my passion and profession, if I could have any other job it would be to own a little paper and stationary store with my soul sister Angie. 

My car is a mess (at least not now thanks to @macks_prodetailing) My desk is a wreck. I call it an organized chaos because I never lose anything. 

Everyone loves champagne, but I would rather have an IV of Savvy B any day. I'm a cheap date and Cupcake is my all time fav. My wine cooler is stocked at all times. 

Most of my emails are in the form of one long run on sentence because I get too excited and distracted to use punctuation. 

I also talk with my hands. A lot.

I have started hundreds of journals and diaries but have never been able to keep it up for longer than a week. 

Pretty sure that if I had a super power, it would be to teleport myself because driving long distances gives me anxiety. 
(All time fav headshot from THE @jessiepreza)

Stations or Buffet. You mean, those are different? They are the same thing, darling and don’t let anyone fool you. There will absolutely still be lines to get food. Your guests will absolutely still go from one to the next with their plate, especially if they are right next to each other. I personally have found a happy medium to this age old question and want to share my experience in stories later today!

It’s totally fine to say that this is a hill I’m willing to die on. There is so much misinformation out there and this is a BIG ONE. We stopped using “buffet” a few years back, in lieu of, we say “stations” now. But, it’s quite literally the same thing. Especially if your venue puts all your “stations” in the same room. So they separated the tables of the buffet? To make it more congested and confusing. If you want stations, AMAZING!! My clients opt for “Strolling” receptions more often than not. The trick though is to separate your stations enough where they aren’t next to each other, double up on one or more for each side of your reception space, use smaller plates, and have lots of options! If you want to know more, send me a DM!

WEDtrade is coming up on August 26th and I want to see YOU there! 

WEDtrade is Jacksonville’s own Wedding Decor Resale Event which means you can either sell your wedding decorations OR shop gently used decor at a fraction of the retail price! From other brides who just got married! You’ll have so much to talk about with all that will be coming! 

Two ways to participate! 

1. SELL - if you just got married, and have wedding, Decour, or details, even dresses or bridal accessories, snag a table to sell! 

2. SHOP - we have a special opportunity for those who want to shop the best deals, register as a VIP shopper and come before we open the doors to the public from 10 AM to 11 AM. 

Register this week and get 50% off your registration! DM me for more details or click the link in profile. 

Huge thank you to @theclaytheatre for hosting us!

Here is the number one reason why your wedding day feels like a blur. 

I’m sure we have all heard the term sensory overload. Your wedding day is the best representation of that. All the sites, all the sounds, all the emotions. It’s almost impossible for your brain to process everything coming at you at once. 

So, do you wanna know why your wedding day will feel like a blur? Because it is. A blur of emotions, a blur of smiling faces, a blur of magnificently fragrant flowers. 

My tip for all brides who are planning their wedding days right now, and working on their timeline and flow of events, if you haven’t started, you should now! Carve out time where it can just be the two of you. Whether that’s a car ride to or from the ceremony to your reception site , if you stolen minutes before introductions where you can take a breath, bustle your dress and eat a couple bites of food. Maybe it’s having a private sweetheart table where are you guys hideaway as dinner is being served and eat by yourselves because no one really will miss you or even though you’re gone. Find the time and make the time. Prioritize this.

The most unbelievable day — we created so many moments for their guests to love, enjoy, and make lifetime memories from. Honored doesn’t begin to describe how I feel about the whole weekend we spent with this family.

When a picture means more now than it could have ever meant before. I know you have heard this before, but photography on your wedding day is THE MOST important element and vendor you will have. Invest in a photographer you love, that is timeless, that captures moments like this one. Because when the day is over, the photos are what you will have to hold on to. I’m so glad that Saville and Chandler chose @ashleysteeby and @21.9films because their families have these precious moments to relive forever and remember just how beautiful she was just a year ago. May we never forget to celebrate the small things and walk with grace and love.

One of my favorite wedding planning stories that I tell is the one of me and Dana. While planning for her wedding at Walkers Landing, all the way from Chicago, we developed an incredible bond through all our emails, FaceTimes, and texts for her day. The strongest bond was our common love for all things @bravotv. After her wedding, we kept in touch. When @theprettymess announced that she was doing @chicagomusical in NYC, we texted and said…”wanna meet up in New York and see the show together?” So here is us, from Wedding Day to New York, and now onto our next adventure in Las Vegas for #bravocon2023!! Can’t believe we are doing this!

It’s not going anywhere and if you know me, you know I’m not really one to hop on a trend…but I am totally hopping on this bandwagon and not getting off any time soon. So ride along with me, you’ll be happy you did! 📸 @everencephotography ✨ @luxepartyrentals 🪄 @lddevents
Attention all 2024 Brides - it’s time to dust off your dancing shoes and start practicing that dip because we are inching closer to YOUR wedding year! Who’s excited?!? This. Girl. Right. Here.

With all these “Wedding Trends for 2024” videos, all I can think about are the trends that are here to stay. Yes, the ROLLOVER trends from 2023 that will still be relevant for all future couples. My favorite will be the champagne tower 🥂 — it’s a great photo op for your photographer, it’s interactive, it also works as a transition from one event to the next that is a non-verbal lead to your guests that we are moving on with the evening or be on the lookout for the next moment of the night! Amazing bride @e.carson.b incredible photographer @wearethebowsers

Why do I love seating charts? It’s a no brainer. Just listen to @lisarinna logic. If your event could run more smoothly, wouldn’t you want that too? Of course they are also a really fun way to incorporate your personality and branding for the wedding!  Don’t listen to others who say that creating a seating plan was so stressful and took hours, that’s just not the case! It doesn’t have to be that way - let me help you! Your guests will thank you, that’s a promise!
